Citation.sAuthor: Torre, J. d. l.[Javier de la]
Citation.sTitle: Study of liquid-liquid equilibria at different temperatures of water + ethanol + 1-butyl-1-methylpyrrolidinium bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl) imide ternary system
Citation.sAbstract: The experimental liquid-liquid equilibria (LLE) data of water + ethanol + 1-butyl-1-methylpyrrolidinium bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl)imide ([bmp][Tf2N]) system has been measured at different temperatures in this work. The LLE of the system has been measured between 283 and 333 K. The UNIQUAC and NRTL models were used to correlate the LLE data of with good results in both cases, however UNIQUAC gave a more accurate correlation. In order to apply UNIQUAC the volume and surface parameters for [bmp][Tf2N] (r, q) were determined. Finally, in order to obtain ethanol from the aqueous mixture, it was checked the solvent capability of ionic liquid and was compared with others from the literature.
